XSS in Product Search
Objective
The goal of this attack was to identify and exploit a Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability in the Product Search functionality of the OWASP Juice-Shop application. By injecting a malicious payload into the search bar, I was able to trigger an alert box, demonstrating the vulnerability.

Tools Used
Web Browser (Firefox): Used for interacting with the Juice-Shop application and triggering the XSS attack via the product search bar.
Methodology
1. Identifying the Vulnerability
I first accessed the Product Search functionality of the Juice-Shop application. This feature allows users to search for products in the store by entering search terms in a search bar.

